description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work on a Unit which opened in March 2017.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit is a Frailty assessment unit (Formally Lister ward), containing 10 inpatient beds 4 assessment areas and Rapid Access clinics running daily Mon-Fri.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We cater for the frail elderly from 65 and above who come in to hospital for various reasons that can be assessed by the full multidisciplinary team who can put in place any systems needed to discharge the patients home within a 72 hour window, and we have a fast turn around of patients within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic motivated band 5 staff nurse&#39;s to join the team, preferably with previous care of the elderly/frailty experience but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must meet the following requirement&#39;s:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To deliver a high quality of care-&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hard working and highly motivated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deborah Peat&lt;br /&gt;deborah.peat@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;01895 279480&lt;/p&gt;
